 The 11th National Games for Persons with Disabilities & the 8th National Special Olympic Games concludes on Friday but the flame in each disabled athletes' heart will never go out. Among 4,484 athletes who featured in the multi-sport gala, visually challenged athletes account for a large proportion. They fought bravely against the darkness. It is the light at the bottom of their hearts that navigated them to victory and glory. Sports have helped them live a colorful life. Produced by Xinhua Global Service 